ukewarm air,\u00a0you may have a duct leak or broken thermostat. Our team will quickly identify and repair the issue\u00a0to restore your home to a comfortable temperature.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Your furnace makes\u00a0<\/strong><strong>strange noises<\/strong><strong>:<\/strong>\u00a0When you turn your furnace on,\u00a0you shouldn\u2019t hear anything other than fans and air. If you hear any bangs or other unexpected noises, call us to get it fixed fast.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Your furnace turns off and on\u00a0<\/strong><strong>constantly<\/strong><strong>:<\/strong>\u00a0If your heating system clicks off and on continuously, there is likely a problem\u00a0with the thermostat, filter, or ductwork\u00a0that requires professional repairs.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>You keep cranking the thermostat up to stay warm:<\/strong>\u00a0If you\u00a0have to\u00a0continually turn up\u00a0the thermostat to get the furnace to generate heat, there\u2019s likely an underlying issue that requires repair.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Strange smells coming from the unit:\u00a0<\/strong>If you notice burning or other unpleasant smells coming from your furnace, there may be overheating components or electrical issues that require immediate repair.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Your pilot light goes out:<\/strong>\u00a0If you notice your furnace pilot light is out,\u00a0contact\u00a0one of our\u00a0HVAC technicians. We\u2019ll make sure there\u2019s no underlying reason the light was extinguished\u00a0and\u00a0get it going again quickly.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>The pilot light is yellow instead of blue:<\/strong>\u00a0A yellow pilot light could indicate a serious problem with your furnace, including a possible\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.tdi.texas.gov\/tips\/how-to-avoid-carbon-monoxide-poisoning-at-home.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">carbon monoxide leak<\/a>.\u00a0Immediately\u00a0turn the furnace off, leave the area, and call our professionals for assistance.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>While&nbsp;some homeowners avoid furnace repair because they\u2019re concerned about how much it will cost or how long it will take, it\u2019s&nbsp;best&nbsp;to deal with these issues head-on.&nbsp;Timely repairs&nbsp;prevent the problem from worsening&nbsp;and save&nbsp;you&nbsp;money in the long run.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Common Furnace Problems We Solve<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Our&nbsp;expert technicians have the skills and experience to tackle any gas or electric furnace repair job that comes our way.&nbsp;Some of the&nbsp;most common furnace problems we see&nbsp;include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Thermostat\u00a0issues<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Faulty ignitors<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ductwork leaks<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Faulty flame sensors<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bad blower motors<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Limited airflow<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Leaking water<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dirty air filters<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Faulty heat exchangers<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>No matter the issue plaguing your unit, our technicians will quickly diagnose it and recommend the best course of action. We\u2019ll consider your budget, heating needs, and unit type to find a lasting solution for your heating system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Our Furnace Repair Process<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We\u2019re proud to&nbsp;offer a full range of gas and electric furnace repair services&nbsp;in Carrollton and surrounding areas.&nbsp;Our technicians receive extensive, ongoing training to ensure they are always up to date on the latest heating technology.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every repair&nbsp;service&nbsp;begins with&nbsp;a&nbsp;complete&nbsp;system inspection and analysis. Once we have identified the problem,&nbsp;we\u2019ll outline&nbsp;your options and our repair recommendations.&nbsp;If your furnace has undergone extensive damage,&nbsp;we may recommend a replacement if we believe this is the more cost-effective solution.&nbsp;We\u2019ll&nbsp;also provide you with an&nbsp;honest and&nbsp;upfront pricing breakdown detailing the cost of repairs,&nbsp;so you stay in the know throughout the entire process.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once we agree on the best solution,&nbsp;we\u2019ll get right to work repairing your furnace.&nbsp;Our technicians always arrive with a fully stocked truck to ensure the shortest service time possible.&nbsp;Before we leave, we will test your unit to check that everything is working&nbsp;correctly&nbsp;and will leave your home exactly as we found it.&nbsp;We\u2019ll be happy to assist if you have any questions throughout the process.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why Choose Medley for Furnace Repair?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>At Medley,&nbsp;we believe in going above and beyond for our customers. We truly care about your family\u2019s comfort and are&nbsp;always&nbsp;ready to&nbsp;address&nbsp;any heating concerns you may have.&nbsp;From the initial phone call to the final cleanup, you\u2019ll receive five-star customer service throughout the entire process.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the top reasons to choose our team for your heating repair include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Transparent pricing:\u00a0<\/strong>We offer up-front estimates and\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/pricing.callmedley.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">honest pricing<\/a>, so you\u2019ll never be shocked by the final bill.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seasoned experts:\u00a0<\/strong>Our licensed technicians are fully trained in the most up-to-date technologies and methods to provide lasting solutions.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Efficient service:\u00a0<\/strong>We\u2019ll always arrive on time and handle the repair as quickly as possible so you can get back to what matters most.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Flexible financing options:\u00a0<\/strong>Furnace repairs can happen unexpectedly and may not fit into your budget. After we provide a quote, we\u2019ll connect you with our financin